<title type="html"><![CDATA[Wireless Controllers]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7910&amp;p=80591#p80591"><![CDATA[
I'm willing to modify the code without charge, but there are a few things that will delay/prevent me from getting it done.<br /><br />*Learning enough PIC assembly to rewrite it for the NES, I'm really only familiar enough with AVR.<br /><br />*Time.  This project is really low on my totem pole.  Even if I were to get $50 or more to do it.  I don't really think it would be right to accept money to write the code.  Mainly because if there were issues someone ran into trying to implement the code I would have to provide support somehow or try to defend my work.  Neither of which seem appropriate for something like this.<br /><br />Plus it's not my code to start with so it wouldn't be right for me to try and make money off his work.<br /><br />If you know the slightest thing about assembly I would recommend learning PIC assembly yourself and taking it on as your own project!  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  It wouldn't be too hard and I'm sure you'd learn a lot.  Even if you didn't know a lick of assembly it would be a good place to start.<br /><br />The main problem with someone already knowing PIC assembly to modify the code is they most likely don't have the parts on hand to test out and debug the code on the actual hardware.  But it's entirely possible for someone to who's really good with it to get everything right the first time.  <br /><br />But like I also mentioned his code has a bug (at least it did for me) where you loose a packet from time to time and it makes it act like all the buttons are pressed when they actually aren't.  I'm not certain it's an issue with the code or that it's a lost/trash packet.  But with the analysis I've done thus far that's what I'm suspecting.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Sun Jun 26, 2011 5:28 pm</p><hr />
