I do this kind of stuff all the time: <br /><a href="http://www.InfiniteNesLives.com" class="postlink">http://www.InfiniteNesLives.com</a><br /> and am actually working on a prototype for those exact controllers right now.  I need to work out a bug though because his code doesn't filter out the one packet that gets lost from time to time if you're more than 12in from the console<br /><br />I right now I'm just making them compatible with the Wii and USB.  I'd like to make them for the NES and SNES as well in the future.  <br /><br />I think you'll have a hard time for that price though.  Are you saying you'd pay $50 for the changes to the code, labor, or parts labor and shipping?<br /><br />There is easily over $50 worth of parts when you think about things like the battery, charger, controller, and dongle.  Not to mention the labor.  My target price for these would be somewhere between $150-$200.  Keep in mind that also gives you a charger that's designed for the battery, not just a dc adapter that will cause the Lithium battery to explode in your hands.<br /><br />I know the price is steep and I wouldn't expect them to fly off the shelves nor would I have to time to make them all if they did.  If you're able and willing to do the work yourself after I get everything working and share the project it might be a better option.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Sun Jun 26, 2011 12:42 pm</p><hr />
